#2.1
#Make a 2D plot of the time-mean TOA longwave, shortwave, and solar radiation for all-sky conditions. 
#Add up the three variables above and verify (visually) that they are equivalent to the TOA net flux.

TOA_longwave = ds2['toa_lw_all_mon']
TOA_shortwave = ds2['toa_sw_all_mon']
Solar_radiation = ds2['solar_mon']
TOA_net_flux = ds2['toa_net_all_mon']
TOA_sum = ds2['solar_mon']-(ds2['toa_lw_all_mon']+ds2['toa_sw_all_mon'])
fields = {0:'TOA_longwave', 1:'TOA_shortwave', 2:'Solar_radiation', 3:'TOA_sum',4:'TOA_net_flux'}

# Set the subgrids
fig = plt.figure(figsize=(24,18), dpi=120)
grid = plt.GridSpec(6,4)  

# Plot each axes
plt.subplot(grid[1,1])  # top left
TOA_longwave.mean(dim=['time']).plot(robust=True)
plt.title(fields[0])

# Plot each axes
plt.subplot(grid[1,2])   # top mid
TOA_shortwave.mean(dim=['time']).plot(robust=True)
plt.title(fields[1])

# Plot each axes
plt.subplot(grid[1,3])  # top right
Solar_radiation.mean(dim=['time']).plot(robust=True)
plt.title(fields[2])

# Plot each axes
plt.subplot(grid[2,1])  # bottom left
TOA_sum.mean(dim=['time']).plot(robust=True)
plt.title(fields[3])

# Plot each axes
plt.subplot(grid[2,2])  # bottom mid
TOA_net_flux.mean(dim=['time']).plot(robust=True)
plt.title(fields[4])

# Show plot
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

#2.2
#Calculate and verify that the TOA incoming solar, outgoing longwave, and outgoing shortwave approximately match up with the cartoon above.
weights = np.cos(np.deg2rad(ds2.lat))
solar_mon_weighted = ds2.solar_mon.weighted(weights)
print(solar_mon_weighted.mean(dim=['time','lat','lon']))
toa_lw_all_mon_weighted = ds2.toa_lw_all_mon.weighted(weights)
print(toa_lw_all_mon_weighted .mean(dim=['time','lat','lon']))
toa_sw_all_mon_weighted = ds2.toa_sw_all_mon.weighted(weights)
print(toa_sw_all_mon_weighted .mean(dim=['time','lat','lon']))

#2.4
#Calculate and plot composites of time-mean outgoing shortwave and longwave radiation for low and high cloud area regions.
#Here we define low cloud area as 25% and high cloud area as 75%. Your results should be 2D maps.
fra=ds2['cldarea_total_daynight_mon']
fields = {0:'shortwave radiation for low cloud area regions', 1:'longwave radiation for low cloud area regions', 2:'shortwave radiation for high cloud area regions', 3:'longwave radiation for high cloud area regions',4:'TOA_net_flux'}

# Set the subgrids

sw_l=ds2.toa_sw_all_mon.where(fra<=25).mean(dim='time').plot( robust=True)
plt.title(fields[0])

# Plot each axes
plt.subplot(grid[1,2])   # top right
lw_l=ds2.toa_lw_all_mon.where(fra<=25).mean(dim='time').plot( robust=True)
plt.title(fields[1])

# Plot each axes

plt.title(fields[2])

多云应增强长波 弱化短波，正确结果如下：¶

high_cloud_global_lw_mean = ds.toa_lw_all_mon.where(ds.cldarea_total_daynight_mon >= 75).mean(dim = 'time').mean(dim = ['lat','lon'])
low_cloud_global_lw_mean = ds.toa_lw_all_mon.where(ds.cldarea_total_daynight_mon <= 25).mean(dim = 'time').mean(dim = ['lat','lon'])
high_cloud_global_aw_mean = ds.toa_sw_all_mon.where(ds.cldarea_total_daynight_mon >= 75).mean(dim = 'time').mean(dim = ['lat','lon'])
low_cloud_global_aw_mean = ds.toa_sw_all_mon.where(ds.cldarea_total_daynight_mon <= 25).mean(dim = 'time').mean(dim = ['lat','lon']) 


out:
high_cloud_global_lw_mean = 251.37349
low_cloud_global_lw_mean = 233.06702
high_cloud_global_sw_mean = 114.74328
low_cloud_global_sw_mean = 88.81645
